Distributor Agreement
This SALES & DISTRIBUTOR AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is made and entered into as of
xxxxx(“Effective Date”), between QMS Resourcing Services Ltd (Registered Number: 03836478) of 141
Cutenhoe Road, Luton, Bedfordshire (“QMSrs”), and xxxxx, Address
NOW THEREFFORE, QMSrs and XXXX hereby agree as follows:
1 PURPOSE
(A) xxx is a Sales & Consultancy company who will market and sell the products of QMSrs in the
geographic area (hereinafter called “TERRITORY”). xxxx will also provide full consultancy services
and after sales support as required by customers employing QMSrs solutions. These customers may
include direct customers of QMSrs at the request of QMSrs.
- TERRITORY Middle East any future territories agreed by both xxx and QMSrs
(B) QMSRS will provide all necessary technical support and after sales service involving replace or
repair of any faulty merchandise. But, QMSrs shall not support the cost of After Sales Service where
the fault is the end user’s or any mishandling of the product by the end user or xxxxx
SALE OF GOODS – PRODUCTS & SERVICES

COMMISSION PAYMENT CONDITION
Commission payments are detailed in Appendix I
PRICE
The price list is established exclusively by QMSRS and may be modified with a 30 days notice. The price
list will be issued to xxxxx immediately after signing of this agreement and an updated price list will be
issued from time to time. An example of the price list model is shown in Appendix I. QMSrs shall also
issue a recommended re-sale price.
In exceptional cases, particularly where a large number of licenses are involved, special prices may be
agreed between xxxxxx and QMSrs for specific customers.
RIGHTS
According to the TERMS and conditions of this agreement, QMSRS guarantees to xxxxx and xxxxx
accepts, the right to represent the PRODUCTS and SERVICES in the TERRITORY during the TERM of
this agreement.
OBLIGATIONS
During this TERM, THE must:
 Promote and sell the PRODUCTS & SERVICES to the best of its knowledge.
 Establish and maintain an adequate sales system.
 Refrain from selling any competitive PRODUCTS & SREVICES.
 Avoid any actions that may cause prejudice to the reputation of QMSrs.
 Supply a quarterly statement on xxxxxxxx’s sales activities.
 Providing updated market information as and when requested by QMSrs.
SALES INFORMATION
QMSRS and THE should share potential sales leads and information promptly.
QMSRS may require, from time to time, certain sales reports or forecasts from xxxxxx.
CONFIDENTIALITY
Xxxxxx must not use or divulge to a third party any confidential information concerning QMSrs, its
PRODUCT or SERVICES. This applies to QMSRS in relation to the information on XXXX.
1.1 INDEMNITY
QMSRS shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless XXXX from and against all claims, demands, liability
and causes of action to the extent arising from QMSRS services.
XXXX shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless QMSRS from and against all claims, demands, liability
and causes of action resulting from misconduct or negligence of XXXX.

RENEWAL
This agreement is automatically renewed at its TERM unless one party wishes to negotiate one or more
herein clauses. In this case, the negotiating party must advise their intention 60 days before the TERM. If
no agreement shall be reached at this TERM, the present agreement shall be canceled.
TERMINATION
This agreement is terminated in one of the following events:
a) Any proceeding, voluntary or involuntary, in bankruptcy or insolvency by or against any party.
b) One of the two parties wishes to cancel this agreement, in this case the party wishing the
termination has to advise the other party 60 days before the termination date.
c) In the event of termination of the Agreement, commissions on any new orders placed during 30-day
notice period will be paid to XXXX.
TERM
This Agreement shall terminate one (1) year after the Effective Date, or may be terminated by either Party
at any time upon sixty (60) days written notice to the other Party. The Receiving Party’s obligations under
this Agreement shall survive termination of Agreement and shall be binding upon Receiving Party’s heirs,
successors and assigns. The Receiving Party’s obligations hereunder shall continue in full force and effect
for one (1) year from the date of disclosure of any such Conditional Information, or until such time as all
Confidential Information disclosed hereunder becomes publicly known and made generally available
through no action or inaction of the Receiver.
On Behalf of XXXX On Behalf of QMSrs Co., Ltd.

APPENDIX I
Commission Payments and Price List
1. Finders Fees (for UK based customers only)
a) If XXXX Group introduce a new customer to QMSrs and XXXX Group do not provide any
further support of any kind to this customer then QMSrs will pay XXXX Group a finders fee
based on a share of the profit generated during the first year of business with the same customer.
Fee will be limited to 2% of the Gross Profit for the first 12 months of business
b) If QMSrs introduce a new customer to XXXX Group and QMSrs do not provide any further
support of any kind to this customer then XXXX Group will pay QMSrs a finders fee based on a
share of the profit generated during the first year of business with the same customer. Fee will be
limited to 2% of the Gross Profit for the first 12 months of business.
2. Consultancy Fees
XXXX shall pay to QMSrs a commission fee of 30% of the sales revenue generated for consultancy
services provided to Customers introduced by QMSrs to XXXX where XXXX is not involved in the sales
process and QMSrs retain ownership of the customer.
